# Huntfact Codebase Rules

- Keep changes minimal and focused on the task; avoid unrelated refactors.
- Preserve existing behavior unless the task explicitly asks for a behavior change.
- Prefer small, readable functions and clear naming over clever abstractions.
- Reuse existing patterns in this repository before introducing a new approach.
- Update nearby docs when behavior, setup steps, or contracts change.
- Validate changes with the smallest relevant checks before finishing.
- Call out assumptions, edge cases, or follow-up work when they are not addressed.
- when asked to implement a plan, first check the `specs/` directory, find the relevant spec, and implement strictly according to that spec before writing code.
- do not make implementation decisions independently when a matching spec exists; follow the spec as the source of truth.
- dont run any code unless explicitly asked
- dont write any documentation explaining your implementation unless explicitly asked
- dont write any test cases unless explicitly asked
